1
00:03:58,670 --> 00:04:04,320
[Justice Is Mine]

2
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:07,420
[Episode 7]

3
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:20,340
Sir, please turn on the radio.

4
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,180
After the financial news
comes the local news.

5
00:04:25,380 --> 00:04:26,420
A shooting incident

6
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:28,340
happened early this morning
in the old town.

7
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:29,460
Police suspect

8
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:31,460
it's connected
to an earlier traffic accident.

9
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:32,300
The deceased

10
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:34,580
is said to be
an 18-year-old surnamed Ma.

11
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:35,780
According to witnesses,

12
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:38,300
several gangsters drove
a champagne-colored car

13
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,500
and parked it in front of Ma's house.

14
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:40,300
Later,

15
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:41,420
two of the gangsters

16
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:42,620
- fired several shots,
- Please pull over.

17
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:44,140
leading to Ma's death from his injuries.

18
00:04:44,540 --> 00:04:46,020
Police are now working fully
to track down the suspects.

19
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:59,220
Who told you to do that?

20
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,700
We got a tip-off call
at midnight yesterday.

21
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:05,100
They gave a name and location this time.

22
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:06,340
Are you sure

23
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:08,500
it wasn't that lunatic, Chi Cheung-wing,

24
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,380
using someone else's hand
to silence him?

25
00:05:10,860 --> 00:05:12,260
The one who died was from the old town.

26
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:13,730
I avenged my brother

27
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:15,220
and Timbo.

28
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:16,100
That's not a loss for me.

29
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:18,100
Who did it?

30
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:20,980
It was for my brother.

31
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:23,260
I must take care of it myself.

32
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,260
The cops will come after you.

33
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:28,300
Let them.

34
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:30,460
I've sorted it all out.

35
00:05:30,860 --> 00:05:31,500
I have nothing to fear.

36
00:05:33,460 --> 00:05:35,740
Do you even realize
the trouble you've caused?

37
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:39,300
You killed that punk,

38
00:05:39,820 --> 00:05:41,260
and you think you're tough.

39
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,220
If it were your brother,

40
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:45,780
he'd have wiped out the whole old town,

41
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:47,180
leaving no one alive.

42
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:55,860
But what matters most

43
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,260
is hoping Gong

44
00:05:58,940 --> 00:06:02,100
can walk out of the hospital
healthy and safe.

45
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:04,580
Your priority

46
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:06,300
is to keep him safe.

47
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:09,460
Do you understand?

48
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:13,660
Answer me!

49
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:18,860
Yes.

50
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:30,780
I need to piss!

51
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:10,860
Chun Yue.

52
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:12,580
Come on in.

53
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:13,740
Okay.

54
00:07:22,260 --> 00:07:24,260
[Eastern District Police Station]

55
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:26,820
Did I make a mistake?

56
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:29,260
I shouldn't have let him out at all.

57
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:32,180
Remember what I said?

58
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:33,860
Getting intel

59
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,900
has to be unexpected.

60
00:07:36,660 --> 00:07:37,780
It's all strategy.

61
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:41,180
You followed the procedure
without breaching any rules, right?

62
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:43,020
Besides,

63
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,560
even if not like this,

64
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:45,640
Ma San-po

65
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,580
would have gotten
bailed out sooner or later.

66
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:48,620
Whoever wanted him dead

67
00:07:49,220 --> 00:07:50,520
would still kill him.

68
00:07:52,140 --> 00:07:53,240
But the issue is no one should've known

69
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:53,900
he was out on bail.

70
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:55,500
On the very first day...

71
00:07:58,140 --> 00:07:59,420
Is it that every word I say

72
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:00,380
is being bugged

73
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:01,100
and leaked out?

74
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:01,700
Okay.

75
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:02,460
Calm down.

76
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:03,580
Talk all you want.

77
00:08:03,580 --> 00:08:05,100
Don't touch anything on my desk,

78
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:05,620
okay?

79
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:08,100
I've never felt
a mole was this close to me.

80
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,740
Every step I take,
they're already one ahead.

81
00:08:11,380 --> 00:08:12,100
Are you scared?

82
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:19,580
You are.

83
00:08:28,740 --> 00:08:30,000
I just saw Chi Cheung-wing.

84
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:32,220
Hon Fui-lung killed someone on his turf

85
00:08:32,260 --> 00:08:33,380
in broad daylight.

86
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:34,780
He will retaliate.

87
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:36,860
I'll send people

88
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,100
to keep 24-hour surveillance on him.

89
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:47,420
Has he woken up?

90
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:48,860
Did he say anything to you?

91
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:50,700
He only told me

92
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:52,020
you're taking him abroad.

93
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:54,100
For the rest,
I need to hear it from you.

94
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,620
I'll take him back first.

95
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:56,460
We can talk about the rest later.

96
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:57,340
Don't go up yet.

97
00:08:57,660 --> 00:08:58,620
Explain everything first.

98
00:08:58,940 --> 00:09:00,180
Why did you tell me

99
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:01,700
not to let Yat-wai go out last night?

100
00:09:04,540 --> 00:09:05,100
Because...

101
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:08,620
he was emotionally unstable
last evening.

102
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:10,780
We argued a little.

103
00:09:11,060 --> 00:09:12,580
Yat-wai is still young.

104
00:09:12,580 --> 00:09:14,340
Why are you suddenly taking him away?

105
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:18,100
I have my reasons.

106
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:20,140
Then explain them clearly.

107
00:09:20,140 --> 00:09:21,420
What happened?

108
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:23,340
Are you hiding something from me?

109
00:09:24,980 --> 00:09:25,460
Yesterday,

110
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:27,100
I went to the bank

111
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:28,580
to deposit some money for Yat-wai.

112
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:29,940
I checked the balance

113
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:31,620
and got shocked.

114
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:34,380
Turns out you withdrew all the money.

115
00:09:34,820 --> 00:09:36,100
What is going on?

116
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:41,580
Can I have some water?

117
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:02,980
Thanks.

118
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:05,860
Go ahead.

119
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:11,140
Not long ago,

120
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:13,540
I found Yat-wai in a relationship
with his teacher.

121
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:16,260
She

122
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,140
is the coach
of the uni basketball team.

123
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:19,700
She's a few years older.

124
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,900
I can't believe this.

125
00:10:23,140 --> 00:10:24,700
They were drinking on campus,

126
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:26,420
and it alarmed the university.

127
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,940
I attended the disciplinary meeting

128
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:30,820
as his parent.

129
00:10:31,140 --> 00:10:32,460
With a female coach?

130
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,900
Maybe he missed his mother so much

131
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:37,900
after Lam died

132
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:39,740
that he wanted someone to confide in

133
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:40,820
and let his feelings out.

134
00:10:55,540 --> 00:10:56,140
Actually,

135
00:10:56,940 --> 00:10:58,380
I also wanted to take Yat-wai to Canada

136
00:10:58,380 --> 00:10:59,100
to study for a semester.

137
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:02,700
So I withdrew all the money.

138
00:11:03,140 --> 00:11:04,500
Are you really willing to go with him?

139
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:06,260
You'd quit your job

140
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:07,660
as a judge?

141
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:09,380
I will.

142
00:11:14,460 --> 00:11:16,340
If you had thought this way,

143
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:18,100
my daughter

144
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,820
wouldn't have committed suicide.

145
00:11:21,260 --> 00:11:23,100
You still owe me an answer about this.

146
00:11:23,660 --> 00:11:24,540
I don't have an answer.

147
00:11:24,540 --> 00:11:25,740
I don't know why either.

148
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,660
I only know I must treat Yat-wai better

149
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:30,860
after Lam died.

150
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,180
What kind of coach is that?

151
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,700
How can she even be called a teacher?

152
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:41,660
She completely disregards ethics.

153
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:43,540
I'm going to report her to the uni.

154
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:44,620
No need.

155
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:45,780
I've taken care of it.

156
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:47,940
Your solution is to pull Yat-wai

157
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:49,060
away from the environment and friends

158
00:11:49,060 --> 00:11:50,220
he's familiar with.

159
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:51,020
Okay.

160
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:52,380
We can discuss

161
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:53,940
whether we are leaving.

162
00:11:54,820 --> 00:11:56,700
Talk it over properly with him.

163
00:11:56,940 --> 00:11:58,460
Stop agitating him.

164
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:00,340
Okay, I will.

165
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:27,980
Let's go.

166
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:29,980
Where to?

167
00:12:31,180 --> 00:12:31,700
Home.

168
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:33,260
Let's go.

169
00:12:38,220 --> 00:12:38,700
Daddy.

170
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,620
Can you tell me what happened?

171
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:46,900
Let's talk at home.

172
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:57,000
Okay.

173
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:58,260
Got it.

174
00:13:00,140 --> 00:13:01,700
No worries, I'll pass it on.

175
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:03,980
Alright, bye.

176
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:07,460
Excuse me,

177
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:10,060
how long do I need to wait
to see Ms. Tong?

178
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:11,660
She's unavailable.

179
00:13:12,340 --> 00:13:13,620
Do you need me to book a time for you?

180
00:13:14,220 --> 00:13:14,860
That won't be necessary.

181
00:13:15,220 --> 00:13:16,260
I'll wait for her.

182
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:24,140
We're back home.

183
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:25,100
Can you

184
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:25,940
tell me now?

185
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:31,820
Have you heard of cautioned statements?

186
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:36,900
When you're not just a witness,

187
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:38,420
but also a suspect,

188
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:40,900
once cautioned by the police,

189
00:13:41,340 --> 00:13:42,460
whatever you say

190
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:44,660
may be used as evidence in court.

191
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:48,820
I was worried I'd slip up

192
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,380
and they'd catch on.

193
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,340
And did they notice?

194
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:56,660
I only confirmed this morning

195
00:13:57,980 --> 00:13:59,260
that they didn't discover anything.

196
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:03,340
I panicked last night

197
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:04,860
and lost my footing.

198
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:09,260
I was terrified that if I were arrested,

199
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,500
you'd be on your own,

200
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:13,580
and eventually

201
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:15,980
even you might be caught.

202
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:20,260
I was too scared to think further,

203
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:22,140
so I wanted to run away.

204
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:24,300
But it's all fine now.

205
00:14:25,540 --> 00:14:26,220
Are you sure?

206
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:30,340
Yes.

207
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:35,380
Sorry.

208
00:15:00,260 --> 00:15:01,530
You have a message.

209
00:15:01,530 --> 00:15:03,340
To listen to it, press 1.

210
00:15:04,540 --> 00:15:05,420
Mr. Chun,

211
00:15:06,380 --> 00:15:07,660
Po won't say anything.

212
00:15:08,180 --> 00:15:09,300
Rest assured, everything's over now.

213
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:29,820
Dad,

214
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,460
shall we order takeaway this afternoon?

215
00:15:33,260 --> 00:15:33,820
Okay.

216
00:15:34,180 --> 00:15:34,980
You order it.

217
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:06,500
Madam Tong.

218
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:11,020
Carry on with this.

219
00:16:13,140 --> 00:16:14,180
What is it, Ms. Chow?

220
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:15,740
Ma San-po was shot dead

221
00:16:15,740 --> 00:16:17,140
while under police protection.

222
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:18,980
There's clearly a mole in your force.

223
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,780
I demand that the police

224
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,740
give an immediate explanation
for his death.

225
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:24,460
The case is still under investigation.

226
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:28,700
You knew full well
he wasn't the real culprit.

227
00:16:29,540 --> 00:16:30,940
He had an alibi.

228
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:33,460
He was pushed out as a scapegoat.

229
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:36,420
The police must act on evidence.

230
00:16:36,660 --> 00:16:37,620
But gangs kill without restraint,

231
00:16:38,060 --> 00:16:39,340
even when they aren't sure
of their target.

232
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:40,660
Tsui Hung being doused in hot oil

233
00:16:40,660 --> 00:16:41,900
proves it.

234
00:16:42,820 --> 00:16:43,620
What's your point?

235
00:16:43,620 --> 00:16:44,340
My point is,

236
00:16:44,660 --> 00:16:46,060
once Ma San-po got bailed,

237
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:47,300
he was sure to face danger

238
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:48,780
and get dragged into the gang feud.

239
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:50,780
Why did you insist on bailing him out?

240
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:51,820
Because I thought

241
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:52,900
you could protect him.

242
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:54,460
Other than the prosecutor and me,

243
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:55,620
you also knew

244
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:56,740
he was going home.

245
00:16:57,180 --> 00:16:58,140
When you openly drove

246
00:16:58,140 --> 00:16:59,220
into the old town,

247
00:16:59,220 --> 00:17:00,660
did you ever think of that?

248
00:17:02,820 --> 00:17:03,900
Offering information

249
00:17:04,460 --> 00:17:05,940
to trade for immigration?

250
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,180
Was it genuine intel,

251
00:17:08,540 --> 00:17:10,020
or were you playing legal tricks?

252
00:17:11,180 --> 00:17:13,380
Only veterans use that kind of trick.

253
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,900
It's not something
a rookie like you could think up.

254
00:17:16,820 --> 00:17:18,100
Who taught you?

255
00:17:34,260 --> 00:17:34,900
Wai,

256
00:17:35,380 --> 00:17:36,460
how long have we been together?

257
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:38,620
The kids are asleep.

258
00:17:38,620 --> 00:17:39,540
Don't wake them.

259
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,780
I don't care if you're still a cop

260
00:17:41,780 --> 00:17:43,460
or if you earn less than before.

261
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:45,540
When we married,

262
00:17:45,660 --> 00:17:47,020
I swore I'd stand by you

263
00:17:47,020 --> 00:17:48,220
no matter what,

264
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,420
as long as the family stays healthy.

265
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:51,820
But you?

266
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:54,580
Have you forgotten your vows?

267
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:57,620
I never thought it'd turn out like this.

268
00:17:57,940 --> 00:17:59,380
If something had happened
to us yesterday,

269
00:17:59,380 --> 00:18:00,740
what about the kids?

270
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:02,820
I didn't think it would be like this.

271
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,420
From the night Po came to our house

272
00:18:04,420 --> 00:18:05,700
until he was taken,

273
00:18:05,820 --> 00:18:07,260
it's been two weeks,

274
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,020
two whole weeks.

275
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:10,460
If you'd thought it through,

276
00:18:10,460 --> 00:18:11,820
that means you don't care

277
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:13,020
about our family's lives at all.

278
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:16,340
Wai, I'm leaving here.

279
00:18:16,340 --> 00:18:17,300
I'm leaving you.

280
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:18,940
Why?

281
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:20,020
I'm taking the kids with me.

282
00:18:20,020 --> 00:18:20,460
Hey,

283
00:18:21,420 --> 00:18:23,740
I just want a safe, peaceful life.

284
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:26,180
After Po's funeral,

285
00:18:26,180 --> 00:18:27,180
I'll take the kids

286
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:28,340
and go to my parents' place.

287
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:29,740
Sa.

288
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:33,700
It's Mr. Chun, right?

289
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,050
Answer it.

290
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:36,580
Ask him

291
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:37,540
if he knows

292
00:18:37,540 --> 00:18:38,700
he's torn our family apart.

293
00:18:38,940 --> 00:18:39,660
Sa.

294
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,340
Don't be like this.

295
00:18:41,340 --> 00:18:42,940
Just because he once helped you,

296
00:18:43,620 --> 00:18:45,300
you'd willingly give up this family

297
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,500
and risk your life for him?

298
00:18:58,780 --> 00:18:59,460
Hello?

299
00:19:02,020 --> 00:19:02,940
My phone ran out of battery.

300
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:05,500
I just heard your message.

301
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:07,180
Didn't you say everything was fine?

302
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:09,140
How did it end up like this?

303
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:10,780
You're asking me?
What am I supposed to know?

304
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:14,660
I'm sorry it turned out this way.

305
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:15,900
Does an apology work?

306
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:17,300
Will Po come back to life?

307
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:24,260
Look,

308
00:19:25,740 --> 00:19:27,500
if Po's family needs anything,

309
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,380
let me know and I'll see if I can help.

310
00:19:29,380 --> 00:19:30,700
I wouldn't dare trouble you.

311
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:32,780
I'm scared someone else might die.

312
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:33,940
Don't call me again.

313
00:19:51,540 --> 00:19:52,100
Master.

314
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:54,860
What is it?

315
00:19:55,540 --> 00:19:57,060
Did I get Ma San-po killed?

316
00:19:58,300 --> 00:19:59,620
I shouldn't have taken your advice

317
00:20:00,060 --> 00:20:01,420
and bailed him out.

318
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:02,900
Then he wouldn't be dead.

319
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:06,420
Have you forgotten what I told you?

320
00:20:06,860 --> 00:20:08,300
You're a lawyer, not a bodyguard.

321
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:11,580
He was only 18 years old.

322
00:20:13,740 --> 00:20:14,940
If it were your son,

323
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:16,740
would you still say that?

324
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:23,860
Lawyers

325
00:20:24,580 --> 00:20:26,100
must keep a distance from their clients

326
00:20:26,340 --> 00:20:27,660
to stay professional.

327
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:30,700
Now the person's dead,

328
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,500
and the case

329
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:33,500
is closed too.

330
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:37,820
It's not closed.

331
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:41,700
Ma San-po wasn't just my client.

332
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:43,820
He was a living person.

333
00:20:50,460 --> 00:20:51,700
I will clear his name.

334
00:21:24,140 --> 00:21:24,440
Come here.

335
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:32,780
Let's go.

336
00:21:33,980 --> 00:21:34,780
Come on, get in the car.

337
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:40,980
Chun,

338
00:21:41,980 --> 00:21:43,140
listen to your mom.

339
00:21:43,980 --> 00:21:45,340
Take good care
of your little sister, all right?

340
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:46,620
Good boy.

341
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:50,540
Chun.

342
00:21:54,060 --> 00:21:54,580
Go.

343
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,180
Come on.

344
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:04,580
Start the car.

345
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:46,140
[Ong Siu, Legislative Council Member]
The shooting that took place today

346
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:48,940
may be another round of fighting

347
00:22:49,140 --> 00:22:50,220
between two opposing gangs.

348
00:22:51,020 --> 00:22:52,700
According to appointed
legislative councillor Ong Siu,

349
00:22:52,980 --> 00:22:54,580
tensions between the old town gang

350
00:22:54,580 --> 00:22:55,900
and the Hons gang

351
00:22:56,340 --> 00:22:57,420
have intensified

352
00:22:57,480 --> 00:22:59,140
following a hit-and-run case

353
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:00,060
two weeks earlier.

354
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,340
According to police information,

355
00:23:02,620 --> 00:23:04,780
the victim of the shooting

356
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:06,580
was an 18-year-old young man
from the old town,

357
00:23:06,580 --> 00:23:07,180
named Ma San-po.

358
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:08,460
And this shooting...

359
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:09,620
Did we get him killed?

360
00:23:13,460 --> 00:23:14,340
Didn't you hear it?

361
00:23:16,220 --> 00:23:18,060
It was an accident
that came out of a gang vendetta.

362
00:23:20,340 --> 00:23:20,980
No one

363
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:22,940
could have stopped an accident.

364
00:23:28,060 --> 00:23:29,300
It's over now.

365
00:23:30,860 --> 00:23:31,940
Let's not talk about it anymore,

366
00:23:31,980 --> 00:23:32,500
okay?

367
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:00,620
Let me have dinner with you tonight.

368
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:03,780
I'm on a vegetarian week.

369
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:06,220
It's fine.

370
00:24:07,460 --> 00:24:09,020
Ying, get him a bowl and chopsticks.

371
00:24:09,540 --> 00:24:09,780
Okay.

372
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:14,900
Mr. Hon Lit,

373
00:24:15,580 --> 00:24:17,180
following Mr. Hon Fui-lung's custom,

374
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:18,500
we'll light memorial candles

375
00:24:18,780 --> 00:24:19,820
and pray for the deceased.

376
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,220
Is that okay?

377
00:24:25,260 --> 00:24:27,380
No wonder you came back
to have dinner with me.

378
00:24:27,660 --> 00:24:29,180
I know you always keep vegetarian

379
00:24:29,740 --> 00:24:31,900
this month for your late family.

380
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:33,940
My father can't be here
for you this year,

381
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:35,340
so let me take his place.

382
00:24:37,660 --> 00:24:38,740
Anything else I do,

383
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:40,220
he probably wouldn't be pleased anyway.

384
00:24:42,580 --> 00:24:43,980
All right, let's eat.

385
00:24:44,180 --> 00:24:50,020
[Fu-Ngam Shantytown Victims' Memorial]

386
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:57,900
Dad, Mom,

387
00:24:58,060 --> 00:24:59,260
[Lum Hon-man, Chow Wai-fong, Lum Wing-hei]
Wing-hei,

388
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:01,500
I'm here to visit you.

389
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:05,860
Don't worry. I'm doing well.

390
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:08,140
[Fu-Ngam Shantytown Victims' Memorial]

391
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:19,140
Twenty years have flown by.

392
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:21,340
That fire

393
00:25:21,660 --> 00:25:23,020
took away 104 lives

394
00:25:23,740 --> 00:25:25,020
and injured 200 others.

395
00:25:26,020 --> 00:25:27,820
Those who survived

396
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:30,700
[Sek Kwong-Cheong]
have gone on with their lives.

397
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:33,020
Many no longer remember

398
00:25:33,060 --> 00:25:35,100
how wrongly their loved ones died.

399
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:37,540
Out of my family of five,
I'm the only one left.

400
00:25:37,980 --> 00:25:39,060
How could I forget?

401
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:41,820
The arsonist may be gone,

402
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,220
but so many people's lives

403
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:44,780
were changed forever.

404
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:46,660
Yours included.

405
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:48,900
I didn't expect that after the fire,

406
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:50,180
you would end up
together with Hon Kui-lung.

407
00:25:50,740 --> 00:25:52,380
He was the only one
willing to take care of me.

408
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:54,940
You've done all right yourself,

409
00:25:55,580 --> 00:25:56,180
becoming a cop.

410
00:25:59,580 --> 00:26:00,360
Haven't heard from Lau Mao?

411
00:26:01,220 --> 00:26:02,700
Since his girlfriend died,

412
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:04,060
he cut all ties.

413
00:26:04,060 --> 00:26:05,540
We all grew up together.

414
00:26:06,460 --> 00:26:07,700
I wonder how he's doing these days.

415
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:09,660
Things have been busy at home.

416
00:26:09,660 --> 00:26:10,180
I'd better get going.

417
00:26:11,620 --> 00:26:12,380
Hey, Lum Chin.

418
00:26:13,820 --> 00:26:15,300
After what happened with Hon Gong,

419
00:26:15,380 --> 00:26:16,900
it must be chaotic out there.

420
00:26:17,580 --> 00:26:19,020
Watch out for yourself.

421
00:26:19,860 --> 00:26:20,780
I'm only a woman

422
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:22,020
beside Lung.

423
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:23,500
I help with the Hon family matters,

424
00:26:23,700 --> 00:26:24,660
take care of his two sons,

425
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,300
and occasionally carry messages for you.

426
00:26:26,820 --> 00:26:28,420
I don't get involved in anything else.

427
00:26:28,660 --> 00:26:30,180
Anyway, just keep yourself safe.

428
00:26:31,220 --> 00:26:31,700
Understood.

429
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:40,620
Mr. Sek.

430
00:26:43,060 --> 00:26:44,500
I thought you wouldn't come today.

431
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:48,460
I said I could empathize,

432
00:26:48,980 --> 00:26:49,780
but this time,

433
00:26:50,700 --> 00:26:51,780
it truly cuts to the bone.

434
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:52,760
Is it

435
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:53,960
about Ma San-bo's case?

436
00:26:56,060 --> 00:26:57,900
People keep saying,
"You get what you deserve."

437
00:26:58,820 --> 00:27:00,060
But is that true?

438
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:02,740
On your side,

439
00:27:02,860 --> 00:27:04,140
hundreds of wrongful deaths

440
00:27:04,140 --> 00:27:05,020
are unavenged.

441
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:06,780
On mine,

442
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:09,340
yet another innocent just died.

443
00:27:11,140 --> 00:27:12,620
Forget about my side.

444
00:27:12,820 --> 00:27:14,140
As police,

445
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,460
we've all faced people we couldn't save

446
00:27:16,660 --> 00:27:17,980
or cases we couldn't solve.

447
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:21,260
I understand.

448
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:23,900
But I still feel awful.

449
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:26,420
I get it.

450
00:27:26,460 --> 00:27:28,300
That's only human nature.

451
00:27:28,460 --> 00:27:29,580
You're human too.

452
00:27:29,780 --> 00:27:30,900
No matter how many times,

453
00:27:30,900 --> 00:27:31,660
it still stings.

454
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:33,740
At least you've got me.

455
00:27:33,740 --> 00:27:35,060
I'm with you, right?

456
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:37,700
Seems it's more like

457
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:38,620
I'm with you today.

458
00:27:38,940 --> 00:27:39,980
Whatever.

459
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,180
As long as

460
00:27:41,420 --> 00:27:43,460
we are together.

461
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:47,820
Then...

462
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:49,900
are we still going there today?

463
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:50,740
Of course.

464
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:53,780
Then it's time to let go.

465
00:27:55,220 --> 00:27:55,700
Why?

466
00:27:56,460 --> 00:27:57,500
There's no one here.

467
00:27:59,820 --> 00:28:02,380
If you don't let go now,
the sun will set when we arrive.

468
00:28:03,980 --> 00:28:04,640
You drive your car.

469
00:28:04,780 --> 00:28:05,260
I'll drive mine.

470
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:07,060
See you in a bit.

471
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:16,700
Lum Chin's family of four

472
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:18,220
and my family of three

473
00:28:18,820 --> 00:28:19,680
are all buried below.

474
00:28:22,820 --> 00:28:24,240
Can the glitter on the surface

475
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:25,020
really cover up

476
00:28:25,100 --> 00:28:26,100
the filth beneath it?

477
00:28:29,980 --> 00:28:30,800
You and Lum Chin

478
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:33,100
both became orphans
because of that fire.

479
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,900
You need her help

480
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,100
to find clues about it,

481
00:28:38,140 --> 00:28:39,340
but you won't tell her

482
00:28:40,140 --> 00:28:41,460
what you're truly investigating.

483
00:28:44,900 --> 00:28:47,180
She is Hon Fui-lung's woman.

484
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:49,420
Her position is sensitive enough.

485
00:28:50,580 --> 00:28:52,020
Investigating cases

486
00:28:52,740 --> 00:28:53,940
is our job as police.

487
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:55,500
There's no need to drag her in.

488
00:28:56,940 --> 00:28:57,740
Speaking of cases,

489
00:28:58,660 --> 00:29:00,100
you know my superior, Mr. Wu,

490
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:01,620
doesn't think much of you, right?

491
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,140
His issue isn't with me.

492
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:05,500
It's with my superior,

493
00:29:05,540 --> 00:29:06,820
Tat Ga-ma.

494
00:29:07,500 --> 00:29:07,940
Hey.

495
00:29:08,540 --> 00:29:10,820
After all, they joined
the force the same year.

496
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,380
Now Tat Ga-ma is Chief Superintendent,

497
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:16,220
while Wu is still
just a Chief Inspector.

498
00:29:17,980 --> 00:29:18,740
Mr. Wu

499
00:29:18,740 --> 00:29:20,580
does dislike the fact that Mr. Tat

500
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:21,960
failed to take harsh action

501
00:29:22,020 --> 00:29:23,260
against the rotten cops.

502
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:24,420
It's not that he wouldn't,

503
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:25,660
but that he couldn't dare.

504
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:26,820
You know,

505
00:29:27,340 --> 00:29:29,060
too many vested interests

506
00:29:29,160 --> 00:29:30,020
are involved.

507
00:29:31,860 --> 00:29:33,860
I don't often hear you defend him.

508
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:37,180
I'm not defending him.

509
00:29:37,620 --> 00:29:38,940
What I mean is,

510
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:40,380
in times like these,

511
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:42,220
being a police officer,
you can't stay that innocent.

512
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,820
But if we can't even trust

513
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,220
our own colleagues,

514
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,060
isn't it a sad thing

515
00:29:52,060 --> 00:29:53,060
to be police?

516
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:54,820
No need to be sad.

517
00:29:56,460 --> 00:29:57,940
You can always

518
00:29:57,940 --> 00:29:58,900
trust me.

519
00:30:42,980 --> 00:30:43,560
Come, sit.

520
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:45,880
Sorry.

521
00:30:47,980 --> 00:30:49,180
I couldn't be with you this year.

522
00:30:50,940 --> 00:30:52,420
Lo Keung has lit memorial candles

523
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:53,900
as you asked.

524
00:30:54,180 --> 00:30:55,300
The thought is what matters.

525
00:30:58,540 --> 00:31:00,500
When Gong recovers,

526
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:02,680
he'll be able
to take care of you for me.

527
00:31:03,980 --> 00:31:05,140
Lit is great, though.

528
00:31:05,540 --> 00:31:06,420
He even came

529
00:31:06,520 --> 00:31:07,780
to have a vegetarian meal
with me last night.

530
00:31:11,100 --> 00:31:12,620
The biggest problem with Lit

531
00:31:13,300 --> 00:31:14,620
is that he's not clever enough.

532
00:31:15,900 --> 00:31:17,180
He doesn't see the bigger picture.

533
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:19,460
If it were Gong,

534
00:31:20,340 --> 00:31:21,740
I wouldn't be so worried.

535
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:23,940
So,

536
00:31:24,580 --> 00:31:26,100
any news on Gong?

537
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:27,580
The doctor says he's stable.

538
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,820
But whether there's progress

539
00:31:29,900 --> 00:31:31,100
depends on his willpower.

540
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:34,660
He is my son.

541
00:31:35,260 --> 00:31:36,460
He will stand up again.

542
00:31:58,540 --> 00:31:59,860
[Starry Series Women's Watch]
I know a friend

543
00:32:00,060 --> 00:32:01,500
who can get you a good discount.

544
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:03,260
What kind of discount?

545
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:05,060
I find it expensive even at 50% off.

546
00:32:06,100 --> 00:32:07,180
That's not too bad.

547
00:32:07,700 --> 00:32:08,660
It looks really nice.

548
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:15,700
I'll get back to work.

549
00:32:18,020 --> 00:32:18,820
What is it?

550
00:32:20,260 --> 00:32:22,060
Looks like my brother's IV
is almost done.

551
00:32:22,660 --> 00:32:23,460
So soon?

552
00:32:24,340 --> 00:32:26,300
It should take another half an hour.

553
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:29,420
Then

554
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:31,020
come over in half an hour.

555
00:32:32,660 --> 00:32:33,060
Sure.

556
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:22,320
Sorry.

557
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:24,620
No worries.

558
00:33:35,740 --> 00:33:36,860
Is my brother

559
00:33:37,980 --> 00:33:38,780
in pain?

560
00:33:42,380 --> 00:33:43,020
Don't worry.

561
00:33:44,340 --> 00:33:45,620
With his brother caring for him,

562
00:33:45,980 --> 00:33:46,980
as the elder one,

563
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:48,780
he can handle this bit of pain.

564
00:33:59,440 --> 00:33:59,900
Thanks.

565
00:34:13,140 --> 00:34:13,980
Excuse me.

566
00:34:14,340 --> 00:34:16,020
Is Ms. Yu here?

567
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:17,620
The one in the pink top is her.

568
00:34:17,940 --> 00:34:18,660
Thank you.

569
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:26,940
Are you Ms. Yu?

570
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:27,820
Yes.

571
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:29,100
My name is Sum Ning.

572
00:34:29,700 --> 00:34:31,100
I'm Chun Yat-wai's grandmother.

573
00:34:32,860 --> 00:34:33,940
What can I do for you?

574
00:34:34,860 --> 00:34:36,020
I've heard

575
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:37,700
about you and Yat-wai.

576
00:34:38,940 --> 00:34:40,500
Are you two in a relationship?

577
